correctness.rationale: The extraction contains many invented or misassigned values, weak traceability, and at least one schema violation. Specific issues: (1) Reactant selection: 'In-Ga bimetallic precursor', O3 as co-reactant for IGZO, and carrier/purging gas (Ar) are not reported in the article; O3 is only mentioned for Al2O3 PL, not for IGZO growth. (2) Supercycle design: IGZO ALD is typically built from In-, Ga-, and Zn-oxide subcycles; representing a single 'InGaZnO' subcycle and omitting a:b:c counts is scientifically inconsistent and not supported by the text. (3) Process parameters: pressure (10 mTorr), dosing times, purge times, flow rates, growth-per-cycle (0.1 Å), number of cycles (50), nucleation period (5 cycles), and 'saturation: True' are not provided in the article. (4) Schema violation: 'plasmaPower': None is type-invalid (should be an object if present); omit if not PEALD. (5) Material properties: optical data (n, absorption, Eg), electrical resistivity, carrier density, mobility, uniformity, conformality, and crystallinity are not reported; roughness 25.3 nm is misassigned (it is the vertical SiO2 sidewall RMS, not IGZO film roughness); elemental concentration '22%' is not in the article; filmDensity 5.4 g/cm3 appears as part of a range (5.9→5.4 g/cm3) depending on surface roughness and is not tied to the specific device film. (6) Device properties: subthreshold swing 95 mV/dec is correct; field-effect mobility (10 cm2/Vs), threshold voltage (−1.5 V), and on/off ratio (1e8) are not reported. (7) While TALD and 200 °C for IGZO and the atomic ratio 0.22:0.25:0.53 are correct, the majority of other fields are ungrounded. To correct: restrict to reported values (TALD, 200 °C, substrate SiO2 spacer, IGZO composition 0.22:0.25:0.53, TCH values including 5 nm, SS 95 mV/dec). Remove or mark unknown (within schema allowances) for precursors/co-reactants, pressure, times, flows, GPC, cycles, nucleation, optical/electrical film properties, uniformity, conformality, and supercycle details; do not assign O3 to IGZO; remove 'plasmaPower' instead of setting None; do not use 25.3 nm as IGZO film roughness.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely ungrounded and incomplete relative to the article and the schema. Many key values are fabricated and not traceable to the text: reactor pressure (10 mTorr), GPC (0.1 Å), number of cycles (50), dosing/purge times and flow rates, nucleation period, uniformity and conformality figures, optical properties (n, band gap), Hall-derived electrical properties (resistivity, carrier density, mobility), on/off ratio (1e8), threshold voltage (−1.5 V), and safety/reproducibility. Several items are misattributed: the 25.3 nm ‘roughness’ reported is the SiO2 spacer sidewall RMS, not IGZO film roughness; ‘O3’ is asserted as IGZO co-reactant but the text only mentions O3 during the Al2O3 protection layer deposition; an ‘In-Ga bimetallic precursor’ for IGZO is not reported. The supercycle design is not represented per the IGZO ALD concept (In2O3/Ga2O3/ZnO sub-cycles); instead a single “InGaZnO” cycle is used without a:b:c counts, which are not provided in the article. Critical ALD processes described in the article are omitted: the Al2O3 protection layer and gate insulator deposited by ALD at 300 °C are not captured as separate processes. Multiple experimental conditions (TCH = 3/5/10/20 nm; TGI = 80/40/15 nm) are not represented as distinct processes or parameterized variants. There is also a schema issue: plasmaPower is set to null, which violates the schema type. What to add/review: (i) add separate ALD processes for Al2O3 PL and GI (300 °C); (ii) for IGZO, provide only grounded parameters (thermal ALD at 200 °C; composition ratio 0.22:0.25:0.53; SS = 95 mV/dec; CDR = 56.4 μA/μm; DIBL = 105.2 mV/V) and remove speculative dosing/flow/pressure/GPC/cycle values; (iii) correct supercycleDesign to list In2O3/Ga2O3/ZnO sub-cycles if available, or omit rather than invent; (iv) correct roughness to reflect what was measured (sidewall RMS) and avoid labeling it as film roughness; (v) avoid unreported optical/electrical material properties and unclear elemental concentrations. Overall, the current record is neither complete nor traceable to the article and contains schema inconsistencies.
